This section documents my SQL Injection testing in DVWA running in a local authorized lab environment.

## What I did

I tested how user input can manipulate SQL queries in a vulnerable login and input fields. I observed how the application responds when malicious SQL payloads are injected.

## What I learned

* How SQL Injection works in web applications
* How unsanitized input affects database queries
* How attackers can extract data using crafted input
* Importance of parameterized queries and input validation

## Key takeaway

Even simple input fields can become entry points for database exploitation if not properly secured.
